http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/HC-judge-recuses-himself-from-hearing-Adi%E2%80%99s-plea/article13996213.ece

Justice Ashok B. Hinchigeri of the High Court of Karnataka on Tuesday recused himself from hearing a petition filed by Upalokayukta Subhash B. Adi, who claimed that the Secretary of the Legislative Assembly cannot seek information on him from any source after admission of motion for removal by the Assembly.When the matter came up for hearing, Justice Hinchigeri said, “Not before me.”. Mr. Adi had claimed in the petition that the Lokayukta or the Upalokayukta cannot be precluded from discharging their duties till the Chief Justice of the High Court submits report finding either of them “guilty” of the charge levelled against them.Now, Mr. Adi’s petition would be placed before the Chief Justice for posting it before another judge for hearing.